SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 46
By Massey
A RESOLUTION to recognize Sally Sparks of Knoxville on being
honored as the 2024 REALTOR of the Year by
Tennessee REALTORS.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly take great pleasure in paying tribute
to those exemplary professionals who have ascended to the very pinnacle of their chosen
professions; and
WHEREAS, Sally Sparks of Knoxville was recently selected as REALTOR of the Year by
Tennessee REALTORS, a most befitting honor that recognizes her career-long dedication to
and significant influence in Tennessee's real estate industry; and
WHEREAS, an accomplished real estate professional with an extensive record of
leadership, community service, and advocacy, Ms. Sparks exemplifies dedication to advancing
the real estate profession, fostering civic engagement, and supporting community; and
WHEREAS, she has been an unwavering supporter of REALTORS Political Action
Committee (RPAC), contributing at the highest levels since 2005, and was recognized as a
Golden R Major Investor and President's Circle sustaining member for multiple years; she was
inducted into the RPAC Hall of Fame at the $25,000 level in 2021 and has attended the
President's Circle Conference many times over the years; and
WHEREAS, Sally Sparks has served in numerous leadership roles within the Knoxville
Area Association of REALTORS (KAAR), including as president (2015), past president (2016),
and NAR director representative to the KAAR Board (2017); her committee work includes her
roles as RPAC chair (2017) and a member of the Grievance, Budget & Finance, and Strategic
Planning committees, among others; and
