WHEREAS, in recognition of her contributions, Ms. Sparks was named KAAR
REALTOR of the Year in 2017; at the state level, her involvement includes thirteen consecutive
years as a Tennessee REALTORS director and serving as Diversity & Inclusion Committee
chair (2023) and Governmental Affairs chair (2020). She has attended every Tennessee
REALTORS Spring Conference since 2008, in addition to numerous conventions; and
WHEREAS, her national involvement includes serving multiple terms as a National
Association of REALTORS (NAR) director and contributing to committees such as RPAC Major
Investor Council, Fair Housing, and Diversity, Equity & Inclusion; she has attended nearly every
NAR Legislative and Annual Conference since 2010; and
WHEREAS, Sally Sparks's civic contributions are vast and include serving on the boards
of the Boys & Girls Club, Wesley House, and CareCuts, through which she has supported
underprivileged and homeless populations; she is a founding member of "100 Realtors Who
Care" and an active volunteer at Faith Promise Church. She has also worked with
Neighborhood Housing, Inc., helping revitalize distressed neighborhoods through her real estate
expertise; and
WHEREAS, her political engagement includes attending local government meetings,
supporting various campaigns, and advocating for REALTOR interests at the state and national
levels; and
WHEREAS, a long-time member of the Women's Council of REALTORS (WCR), Sally
Sparks has served as local chapter president (2010, 2021) and as the Tennessee Member of
the Year (2018); she has held various roles within the Residential Real Estate Council (RRC),
including Tennessee State president (2019) and National RVP Sub Selection Committee chair
(2022), and she is a member of REBAC, AREA, and the Real Estate Business Institute (REBI);
and
- 2 - 002093

WHEREAS, throughout her career, Ms. Sparks has been recognized for her tireless
efforts to elevate the real estate profession and give back to her community; her contributions to
RPAC, her leadership roles, and her commitment to diversity, inclusion, and civic service
exemplify the highest standards of excellence in the field; and
WHEREAS, Sally Sparks continues to inspire her peers with her unwavering
commitment to the REALTOR mission and her community, and she is richly deserving of our
approbation on this special occasion; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we recognize Sally Sparks of Knoxville on being
honored as the 2024 REALTOR of the Year by Tennessee REALTORS and extend to her our
best wishes for much continued success in all her future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
